          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">γελάω, γελόω</span></b> , part. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">γελόωντες, γελώοντες</span>, ipf. 3 pl. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">γελώων</span>, aor. (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐ</span>)<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">γέλἁσ̓σεν</span>, 3 pl.
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">γέλἁσ̓σαν</span>, part. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">γελἅσ̓σᾶς</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">laugh</span>, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἡδύ</span>, ‘heartily;’ <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἁπαλόν, ἀχρεῖον, δακρυόεν, χείλεσιν</span>, only ‘with the
          lips,’ i. e. not from the heart, <i><span class="en">Il.
            15.101</span></i>; fig., <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">γέλασσε δὲ πᾶσα περὶ
